cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.GT 

This paper deals with the study of voting behavior and power in an online democracy platform, which involves the use of algorithms and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the intersection of computer science and social issues. The paper also involves the use of statistical analysis and power indices, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another likely category. The study of power distribution and voting behavior also falls under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The paper also involves the analysis of data and the use of algorithms, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the study of power indices and their effectiveness falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
